            <title>About Me</title>
            <link>http://localhost:53376/about/</link>
            <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
            <guid>http://localhost:53376/about/</guid>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello! I am &lt;strong&gt;Chandan Kumar&lt;/strong&gt;, a software engineer with a deep passion for building secure, scalable, and impactful software solutions.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Currently, I am working at a &lt;strong&gt;leading Japanese cyber security company&lt;/strong&gt;, where I focus on developing advanced security tools and infrastructure. Prior to this, I honed my skills as an &lt;strong&gt;SDE-iOS&lt;/strong&gt; at a dynamic &lt;strong&gt;Silicon Valley company&lt;/strong&gt;, working on cutting-edge mobile applications.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;the-intersection-of-tech--humanities&#34;&gt;The Intersection of Tech &amp;amp; Humanities&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;My academic background is somewhat unique in the tech world. I hold &lt;strong&gt;Master&amp;rsquo;s degrees in both Computer Science and Political Science&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This dual perspective allows me to approach technical problems with a broader context, understanding not just &lt;em&gt;how&lt;/em&gt; to build technology, but &lt;em&gt;why&lt;/em&gt; it matters and how it impacts society, business, and governance.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;writing--interests&#34;&gt;Writing &amp;amp; Interests&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;When I&amp;rsquo;m not writing code, I&amp;rsquo;m writing articles. I love to explore and articulate thoughts on a wide range of topics, including:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Computer Science&lt;/strong&gt;: Deep dives into algorithms, system design, and security.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Humanities&lt;/strong&gt;: Reflections on history, politics, and social dynamics.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Studies&lt;/strong&gt;: Analyzing market trends and economic principles.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interesting Facts&lt;/strong&gt;: Curating and sharing fascinating knowledge from various fields.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;projects--open-source&#34;&gt;Projects &amp;amp; Open Source&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;I am an active contributor to the open-source community and have developed several applications. Here are a few of my notable projects:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://optionallabs.com/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;    &gt;Optional (iOS/Android)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://github.com/ckdash-git/ColorsKit&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;    &gt;ColorsKit (iOS)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://github.com/ckdash-git/ScreenShield&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;    &gt;ScreenShield (iOS)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m always open to connecting with fellow engineers, thinkers, and creators. Please feel free to reach out or follow my work through the links below.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;social-menu-shortcode&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;ul class=&#34;menu-social&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &#xA;            &lt;li&gt;&#xA;                &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.linkedin.com/in/ckdash/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener noreferrer&#34; title=&#34;linkedin&#34;&gt;&#xA;                    &lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; class=&#34;icon icon-tabler icon-tabler-linkedin&#34; width=&#34;24&#34; height=&#34;24&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; stroke-width=&#34;2&#34; stroke=&#34;currentColor&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34; stroke-linecap=&#34;round&#34; stroke-linejoin=&#34;round&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;path stroke=&#34;none&#34; d=&#34;M0 0h24v24H0z&#34; fill=&#34;none&#34;/&gt;&#xA;  &lt;rect x=&#34;4&#34; y=&#34;4&#34; width=&#34;16&#34; height=&#34;16&#34; rx=&#34;2&#34; /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;line x1=&#34;8&#34; y1=&#34;11&#34; x2=&#